Hello,<br>
<br>
I have a DataGrid with two columns:<br>
<span id=UniqueID1226572809629>
<pre> &lt;dg:DataGridTemplateColumn Header=&quot;Start&quot; Width=&quot;100&quot;&gt;
  &lt;dg:DataGridTemplateColumn.CellTemplate&gt;
      &lt;DataTemplate&gt;
         &lt;TextBlock Text=&quot;{Binding Name}&quot; TextAlignment=&quot;Right&quot; TextWrapping=&quot;Wrap&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;
   &lt;/dg:DataGridTemplateColumn.CellTemplate&gt;
   &lt;dg:DataGridTemplateColumn.CellEditingTemplate&gt;
      &lt;DataTemplate&gt;
         &lt;TextBox Text=&quot;{Binding Name}&quot; AcceptsReturn=&quot;True&quot;  Padding=&quot;0&quot; TextWrapping=&quot;Wrap&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;
   &lt;/dg:DataGridTemplateColumn.CellEditingTemplate&gt;
&lt;/dg:DataGridTemplateColumn&gt;
                       
&lt;dg:DataGridTextColumn Header=&quot;- Name -&quot; Width=&quot;200&quot; Binding=&quot;{Binding LastName}&quot; &gt;
/dg:DataGridTextColumn&gt;</pre>
</span>
<pre></pre>
<br>
When I run the program the grid is displayed with data. I can use the arrow keys to move between cells. But when I want to edit cell data and press F2, this does not work properly with the TemplateColumn. The TextBox is displayed, but without a caret.I have to click the TextBox once with the mouse before I can enter any text.<br>
<br>
The &quot;normal&quot; DataGridTExtColumn behaves as expected. F2 shows the TextBox, there is a caret and I can just type some text.<br>
<br>
<br>
Norbert Ruessmann
